no-compare-neg-zero.description:
Description

The rule should warn against code that tries to compare against-0, since that will not work as intended. That is, code likex === -0will pass for both+0and-0. The author probably intendedObject.is(x, -0).

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-compare-neg-zero: "error" */

if (x === -0) {
    // doSomething()...
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-compare-neg-zero: "error" */

if (x === 0) {
    // doSomething()...
}

/* eslint no-compare-neg-zero: "error" */

if (Object.is(x, -0)) {
    // doSomething()...
}
